                            <comment id="134660" author="pjones" created="Fri, 27 Nov 2015 19:55:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think that this ticket is well out of date &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="62705" author="bogl" created="Mon, 22 Jul 2013 15:20:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We may want to skip past -358.11.1 and go directly to -358.14.1.  There is already a mod in progress to update master to -358.14.1; &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/7055&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/7055&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="62417" author="bogl" created="Tue, 16 Jul 2013 19:47:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/7010&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/7010&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="62416" author="bogl" created="Tue, 16 Jul 2013 19:39:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As far as I can see no functional changes are needed.  I can configure and build --disable_server against the newest el6 kernel just fine.  I will push a patch to update ChangeLog and target files to the newer version.  Don&apos;t think anything more is necessary.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="62407" author="pjones" created="Tue, 16 Jul 2013 18:38:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bob&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please look into what would be required to add client support to b1_8 for the latest RHEL6.4 kernel update?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
